parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to steer, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff
the vehicle pulls in either direction
the brake pedal has to be pressed very hard to stop the vehicle
abnormal odor inside the cabin
power steering fluid leak
loss of power steering functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop as needed, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop as needed
the brake pedal has to be pressed very hard to stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic system can cause the power steering and brake systems to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Power steering fluid leak
brake fluid leak
loss of power steering functionality
failure of the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is not in the driver's control.
symptoms: The vehicle moves unexpectedly
often in reverse
when the driver is not in the driver's seat or when the transmission is in Park
potentially causing damage to property or injury to people in the surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission shift interlock can allow the vehicle to move unexpectedly, even when the transmission is in Park, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle moves unexpectedly
often in reverse
when the driver is not in the driver's seat or when the transmission is in Park
potentially causing damage to property or injury to people in the surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, and cause inconvenience and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive notification of a recall but are unable to have the repair performed due to part unavailability
dealerships are unable to schedule appointments or complete repairs
owners are advised to contact different dealerships
manufacturers are not aware of the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of trailer brakes and lights can lead to a loss of control while towing, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Trailer brakes and lights do not function consistently
sometimes working and sometimes not
causing uncertainty and unpredictability while towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ineffective Recall Repair for Trailer Brake and Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffective recall repair can lead to continued malfunction of trailer brakes and lights, prolonging the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Dealership informs customers that the initial recall repair does not work
and a new fix is needed
leaving customers without a reliable solution
especially during critical towing periods.
